---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import H1 from "../components/typography/H1.astro";
import H2 from "../components/typography/H2.astro";
import Link from "../components/typography/Link.astro";
---

<Layout title="Useful resources" description="Useful resource, tutorials, podcasts etc.">
  <H1>Useful resources</H1>
  <section class="my-4">
    <H2>Podcasts</H2>
    <ul class="my-4 list-disc">
      <li>
        Syntax podcast hosted by <b>Wes Bos</b> and <b>Scott Tolinski</b>
        <Link href="https://syntax.fm/" external> [https://syntax.fm/] </Link>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lYXYmcDjGMA" external>
              AI Superpowers with Kevin Hou and Codeium
            </Link>
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GVY__H89Ysk" external
              >Local AI models in JavaScript, with Xenova of Transformers.js</Link
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <section class="my-4">
    <H2>Tutorials</H2>
    <ul class="my-4 list-disc">
      <li>
        WebRTC tutorials by <b>Seungmin Lee</b>
        <Link href="https://millo-l.github.io/WebRTC-implementation-method-Mesh-SFU-MCU/" external>
          [https://millo-l.github.io/WebRTC-implementation...]
        </Link>
        <br />
        It's a great starting point for learning WebRTC. I used it as a reference for my own PoC audio
        chat that I had to create for a client.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <section class="my-4">
    <H2>Code style, development process, good practises..</H2>
    <ul class="my-4 list-disc">
      <li>
        Conventional commit messages
        <Link href="https://gist.github.com/qoomon/5dfcdf8eec66a051ecd85625518cfd13" external>
          [https://gist.github.com/qoomon/...]
        </Link>
      </li>
      <li>
        useState pitfalls series by <b>tkdodo</b>
        <Link href="https://tkdodo.eu/blog/putting-props-to-use-state" external>
          [https://tkdodo.eu/blog/putting-props-to-use-state]
        </Link>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Layout>
